A vintage 1980s-style illustration of a sleek silver lotus flower emerging from a cascading waterfall of golden curly braces, brackets, and colons that form abstract JSON-like patterns. The lotus petals are made of translucent circuit board traces with tiny glowing nodes. The scene is set against a warm sepia-toned background with subtle grid lines reminiscent of old spreadsheet paper. Soft amber and teal lighting creates depth, with the data stream flowing from an antique brass computing machine at the top, transforming into organic botanical forms as it descends. The overall mood is nostalgic yet forward-looking, blending natural elegance with retro-futuristic technology aesthetics. Warm film grain texture throughout.
